  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d2847.gif" alt="rayonne" border="0" height="108" /></a><br /><em>Flag and Arms of <a href="no-20-30.html">S�r-Varanger</a>, Norway (fotw); Flag 
  of 
  <a href="no-20-24.html">Berlev�g</a>, Norway (fotw)</em><hr /><a name="rays"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">RAYS (or RAYED)</dt>
  <dd>1) The terms sometimes (and correctly) used in place of pointed to describe the 
  number of such points on a sun emblem &ndash; see &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvs8.html#sunemblem">sun emblem</a>&rsquo; and 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvp5.html#pointed">pointed</a>&rsquo; (also 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dv-a.html#active">active</a>&rsquo;, 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dv-a.html#activeandinactive">active and inactive</a>&rsquo;, and 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvi2.html#inactive">inactive</a>&rsquo;).<br />
2) See &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvb4.html#beams">beam(s) 1)</a>&rsquo;.
